  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The primary objective of the study is to demonstrate the superiority of an &quot;early tips&quot;
      strategy over standard treatment by glue obliteration (G0) in preventing bleeding recurrence
      or death at one year after a non GOV1 gastric variceal bleeding in cirrhotic patients
      initially treated by GO.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
